# Lumina — project rules

Lumina is a reflection app. Keep the UX calm and focus-friendly; no busy dashboards in this phase.

Visual identity: blue-green palette (`lumina-900` through `lumina-100`). See the `tailwind-styling` rule for usage.

## Language

- UI copy, labels, error messages, and placeholders in **Dutch**.
- Use **je** consistently (informal but warm).

## Folder structure

```
app/
  (marketing)/     # landing, about — optional
  (app)/           # app shell (layout + nav)
components/
  ui/              # reusable primitives (Button, Input, Card)
  [feature]/       # domain-specific, e.g. journal/ later
lib/
  types/
  utils/
```

## Scope

Do not add database, auth, or AI logic until explicitly requested.

## Naming

- Components: PascalCase
- Route folders: kebab-case
- Functions and variables: camelCase

## Next.js

When in doubt, read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` — see also `AGENTS.md`.
